Parliament, Thursday 08 October 2020 – National Assembly Speaker Ms Thandi Modise will deliver the 2020 Raymond Mhlaba Centenary Memorial Lecture today at 17h00.
	
	The lecture, an annual event of the Eastern Cape Provincial Legislature, was started in 2016 to honour the enormous contribution of Raymond Mhlaba – the inaugural Premier of the Eastern Cape and a Rivonia trialist who spent 25 years in Robben Island after he was convicted with Nelson Mandela, Govan Mbeki, Walter Sisulu and others
	
	Speaker Modise will reflect on the life and times of Oom Ray, as Raymond Mhlaba was affectionately known, in relation to strengthening public sector governance, accountability and service delivery.
	
	Details of the virtual Public Lecture:
	
	Date: Thursday, 08 October 2020
	Time: 17.00 – 19.00
	Virtual Platform: Microsoft Teams
	
	Members of the media who would like to observe the Public Lecture may forward their contact details to Mlindi Mpindi on email mmpindi@parliament.gov.za for inclusion in the Parliamentary Communication Services WhatsApp Group, where login details will be shared. Journalists are urged to forward the request using their official email addresses (no private emails).
	
	Members of the public may follow the Lecture live on Parliament TV (DSTV Channel 408), via live stream on the Parliament YouTube channel and Twitter page on the links below. You may subscribe to the Parliament YouTube channel to receive instant notification of live feeds.
	
	Twitter: https://twitter.com/ParliamentofRSA
	Facebook: https://facebook.com/ParliamentofRSA
	YouTube: https://www.youtube.com/ParliamentofRSA
	
